{
  "stem": "4967.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And when the day came in, my Bar Mitzvah, I had to remember mitzvah [NON-ENGLISH] 5 o'clock in the morning, we made my service, and it's a [INAUDIBLE] part of me. 6 o'clock, the men had to go to work, and from nowhere the Germans walk into the synagogue and shouted, everybody, [SPEAKING GERMAN], get out, get out, get out.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I, with my great uncle Irs, went-- we walked to my mother's place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we came to  our apartment in the block, in the block, in the block of flats.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she took out a piece of bread for me and for my great uncle, Irs Miller, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and she spoke to me.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She said, according to the Jewish Bible, today you became a man.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And she gave me a piece of bread, maybe milk or some other thing to drink, and she blessed me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And  my-- Irs Miller blessed me too, and he say, [NON-ENGLISH], and he went back to his flat or house.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I can't remember where he stayed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And this was my Bar Mitzvah.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I had no party, I had no musical instruments going on, only fear.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Fear from the Germans, fear from hunger, and fear from disease.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Fear that nobody can put it in words and writing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It's a feeling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's like the world falls on you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's--people asked me after the war, how did you feel?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I say, I can't describe-- I can't explain to you how you feel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's most terrible thing, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even a person when he dies, he comes to his place when he doesn't know already that he dies.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's terrible.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People used to die, just die in the street, die in the flat.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
